13 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
14 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
15 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 105.34 of Title 82, unless there
16 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
17 A. The Oklahoma Water Resources Board is hereby directed to
18 conduct a comprehensive study on the water flow of the Kiamichi
19 River. The study shall include, but shall not be limited to, the
20 following:
21 1. Assessment of the river's flow rates throughout the year
22 under varying conditions, including periods of drought and flood;
23 2. Evaluation of the minimum flow required to maintain the
24 river's ecological health and integrity;
Req. No. 10124 Page 1

1 3. Determination of the flow capacity necessary to allow for
2 permitting the removal of water from the river without causing
3 adverse impacts to the environment, existing water rights, and
4 downstream users; and
5 4. Analysis of the potential effects of constructing and
6 operating a low-water dam on the river, including:
7 a. hydrological impacts on water flow and sediment
8 transport,
9 b. ecological effects on fish, wildlife, and riparian
10 habitats, and
11 c. implications for recreational activities and local
12 communities.
13 B. The Board shall submit a final report detailing the findings
14 of the study and any recommendations for legislative or regulatory
15 actions to the Governor, the President Pro Tempore of the Oklahoma
16 State Senate, and the Speaker of the Oklahoma House of
17 Representatives. The report shall be due no later than December 31,
18 2026.
19 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2025.
